總會出現反對現存規範的案例

36
00:02:01.450 --> 00:02:03.320
to adopt its opposite.
總會出現反對現存規範的案例

37
00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:06.990
So there's never rule that you can follow
that will differentiate between science
所以不存在能準確劃分科學與偽科學的標準

38
00:02:06.990 --> 00:02:09.150
and pseudoscience, anything goes.
他的名言是”諸行皆可“(anything goes)。

39
00:02:11.650 --> 00:02:16.190
If we draw in inferences from data,
then there are logical ways to do this and
根據資料做推論，有邏輯與非邏輯的方法

40
00:02:16.190 --> 00:02:18.270
illogical ways to do this.
根據資料做推論，有邏輯與非邏輯的方法

41
00:02:18.270 --> 00:02:23.720
In propositional logic, one valid rule of
inference is known as the Modus Tollens.
能做有效推論的一種邏輯方法是否定後件(Modus Tollens)

42
00:02:23.720 --> 00:02:26.520
In other words, denying the consequents.
簡單說就是否定推論得到的結果

43
00:02:26.520 --> 00:02:27.110
Let's take a look.
簡單說就是否定推論得到的結果

44
00:02:28.420 --> 00:02:34.000
If the Modus Tollens is used we have
a line of reasoning that goes as this.
否定後件能寫成這樣的形式

45
00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:37.960
If p then q, not q, therefore not p.
若p則q，非q
所以非p

46
00:02:38.990 --> 00:02:40.490
Let's make it a little bit more concrete.
來看看這條規則的實際用處

47
00:02:41.630 --> 00:02:44.950
If we have a theory,
then we should observe some data.
根據要驗證的理論，我們收集需要的資料

48
00:02:46.050 --> 00:02:51.020
Then we collect some data but we do not
observe the data that we predicted.
但是收集到的資料不符合理論的預測

49
00:02:51.020 --> 00:02:58.089
From this we can deny the consequent,
therefore not the theory.
根據否定後件的規則，推論理論不成立

50
00:02:58.089 --> 00:03:01.846
A very often illogical way of drawing
inferences is known as affirming
另一方面就是採取非邏輯方法
從肯定的角度進行推論

51
00:03:01.846 --> 00:03:03.100
the consequent.
另一方面就是採取非邏輯方法
從肯定的角度進行推論

52
00:03:03.100 --> 00:03:06.180
Now this is not a valid rule of
inference although it's tempting to use.
雖然這種方法有時有用
卻非有效的推論規則

53
00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:14.060
It goes like this,
if p then q we observe q therefore p.
寫成邏輯形式就是
若p則q，觀察到q，所以p成立。

54
00:03:15.510 --> 00:03:18.500
Now this might look like it's logical but
it isn't.
雖然這像是邏輯規則，其實不是

55
00:03:18.500 --> 00:03:19.640
Let's look at some more detail.
讓我告訴你為什麼

56
00:03:20.950 --> 00:03:23.810
If we have a theory then we
should observe some data,
為了確認手上理論為真，我們必須收集資料

57
00:03:24.810 --> 00:03:29.360
we observe the data and then we conclude
that therefore the theory is true.
收集到的資料要用來確認理論為真

58
00:03:30.530 --> 00:03:33.780
Now this might still look
like it's valid but it isn't.
這樣的命題推理似乎有效，其實不然

59
00:03:33.780 --> 00:03:36.060
Let's make it even more concrete.
讓我用更明確的例子

60
00:03:36.060 --> 00:03:41.416
Let's say that I conclude that if
I'm a man then I'm also a human.
我說“若我是男人，那我也是人類”

61
00:03:41.416 --> 00:03:46.171
I observe that I am a human and then I
conclude that therefore I must be a man,
我觀察到我是人類，所以結論我是男人

62
00:03:46.171 --> 00:03:48.655
but this last step is not valid.
這樣的推論其實無效

63
00:03:48.655 --> 00:03:51.077
I could also be a woman or
anything in between.
因為我也可以是女人或跨性別者

64
00:03:53.683 --> 00:03:56.959
A theory can be either refuted or
corroborated but
一個理論可以被證明為錯，或有證據證成

65
00:03:56.959 --> 00:03:59.430
you can never prove a theory.
但不能直接推論為真

66
00:03:59.430 --> 00:04:00.310
Now this is important.
這個認識很重要

67
00:04:00.310 --> 00:04:03.350
We can never have certain knowledge.
我們不會有肯定的知識

68
00:04:03.350 --> 00:04:06.490
We can aim for it but
we can never achieve it.
這個目標可以努力但永遠無法達成

69
00:04:06.490 --> 00:04:10.730
It's easier to refute a theory and this is
based on Popper's idea of falsification.
波普的否證論概念就是證明理論為錯較容易

70
00:04:10.730 --> 00:04:13.930
So you can have a conclusion
where you falsify a prediction.
只要否證一個預測就會有結論

71
00:04:16.310 --> 00:04:22.670
For example, if we look at the prediction,
all swans are white, now, no number
例如這一則預測：
所有天鵝都是白的，就算不知道白天鵝有多少隻

72
00:04:22.670 --> 00:04:28.240
of sightings of white swans can ever prove
the theory that all swans are white.
永遠可以宣稱這個預測為真

73
00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:30.570
However, if we only see one black swan,
但是，只要今天看見一隻黑天鵝

74
00:04:30.570 --> 00:04:34.250
this will disprove our theory
that all swans are white.
這個預測就會被推翻

75
00:04:34.250 --> 00:04:38.960
So you see that falsification is
a very potent tool to reject theories.
由此可見否證論推翻理論的威力

76
00:04:38.960 --> 00:04:44.070
Now we can never accept them, we can
observe observations that are in line with
反過來說，即使無法完全證明理論為真，

77
00:04:44.070 --> 00:04:45.710
our theory but we can never prove it.
只要獲得的資料與預測一致，理論還是可能為真

78
00:04:47.680 --> 00:04:51.330
However, when we use inferences
based on statistics,
然而在統計推論的場域

79
00:04:51.330 --> 00:04:56.080
then falsifications are never really black
or white, as the case with black swans.
並不像黑天鵝問題一樣有非黑即白的否證

80
00:04:56.080 --> 00:04:58.622
If you see a black swan and
you have a clear view,
看見黑天鵝是鐵錚錚的否證證據

81
00:04:58.622 --> 00:05:02.040
then you can be pretty sure
that this is not a white swan.
看見黑天鵝是鐵錚錚的否證證據

82
00:05:02.040 --> 00:05:06.090
You might even get a feather and try to
wash it, see that the black doesn't come
如果你很龜毛，可能會洗洗看
黑天鵝的羽毛會不會掉色

83
00:05:06.090 --> 00:05:10.180
off and then you have a solid
observation that black swans exist.
再決定要不要接受這個證據

84
00:05:10.180 --> 00:05:12.750
In statistics we always
work with probabilities.
統計則是依賴機率

85
00:05:12.750 --> 00:05:16.571
We have a certain probability that the
data we have observed, is surprising for
資料的否證程度全賴歸察到的機率

86
00:05:16.571 --> 00:05:17.510
example.
資料的否證程度全賴歸察到的機率

87
00:05:17.510 --> 00:05:21.750
We have a certain probability
that there is no true effect.
只能斷言沒有真實效果的機率

88
00:05:21.750 --> 00:05:24.540
Now this kind of statements
are never completely black or white.
這樣的結論永遠不會非黑即白

89
00:05:24.540 --> 00:05:27.427
So it's always more difficult
to falsify a prediction.
所以任何統計的預測被否證的難度頗高

90
00:05:29.050 --> 00:05:34.000
Furthermore, we wonder whether we
actually reject theories after
更進一步的說，理論很難被一種否證證據推翻

91
00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.640
a single falsification.
更進一步的說，理論很難被一種否證證據推翻

92
00:05:36.640 --> 00:05:39.270
And Lakatos argues that we never do this.
拉卡托斯指出不可能有這樣的否證

93
00:05:39.270 --> 00:05:41.790
People have some sort of feeling for
a theory.
想出理論的方式有很多種

94
00:05:41.790 --> 00:05:44.810
They like a specific theory and
they want it to be true.
有的理論的目標很特定

95
00:05:44.810 --> 00:05:46.020
And this is perfectly fine.
只要不被特定的證據推翻就好

96
00:05:46.020 --> 00:05:48.629
You can try to find support for
it in different ways.
支持理論的證據也是各式各樣

97
00:05:50.230 --> 00:05:53.990
Now there are good reasons
to stick with the theory.
測試理論會不會被推翻其實很有意義

98
00:05:53.990 --> 00:05:58.660
When a theory makes a very, very good
predictions then a single observation
如果能用理論做個好預測

99
00:05:58.660 --> 00:06:02.680
that's not in line with your predictions
is no reason to give up the entire theory.
然後獲得不支持理論預測的證據
就可以毫無懸念的放棄理論。

100
00:06:03.730 --> 00:06:06.430
This statement by Stevens is rather nice.
Stevens的這段話說得很好

101
00:06:06.430 --> 00:06:11.880
It says, the lesson of history is that
a bold and plausible theory that fills
科學史上有許多大膽又合理的理論

102
00:06:11.880 --> 00:06:17.050
a scientific need is seldom broken by the
impact of contrary facts and arguments.
被反證的事實與言論擊倒

103
00:06:17.050 --> 00:06:21.650
Only with an alternative theory can
we hope to displace a defective one.
而且總是有新的理論取代舊理論的位置

104
00:06:21.650 --> 00:06:25.790
So it's perfectly fine if you
sometimes observe a finding
如果你能發現和你的理論預測不同的證據其實是好事

105
00:06:25.790 --> 00:06:27.890
that's not in line with
theoretical predictions.
如果你能發現和你的理論預測不同的證據其實是好事

106
00:06:27.890 --> 00:06:30.040
You don't have to throw your
theory out of the window.
你不必直接捨棄理論。

107
00:06:31.300 --> 00:06:34.960
If you have a strong theory that makes
good predictions in other fields,
如果原來理論的預測在其他地方經得起考驗

108
00:06:34.960 --> 00:06:38.280
there's no reason to give it up
until you have a better theory.
依然可以堅持到有更好的理論出現

109
00:06:40.690 --> 00:06:42.230
So if there's a falsification,
如果理論的預測被否證

110
00:06:42.230 --> 00:06:47.210
if one of these predictions don't hold
up then what is exactly falsified?
代表理論本身被否證嗎？

111
00:06:47.210 --> 00:06:50.960
Is it the theory itself or
there are auxiliary theories.
被否證的是理論本體還是附屬命題？

112
00:06:50.960 --> 00:06:55.490
Assumptions that you make about the data
collection process, for example.
設想你做了一次資料收集

113
00:06:55.490 --> 00:06:57.820
Now let's say you do
an experiment on some people and
像是根據一個理論預測，找些人做了實驗

114
00:06:57.820 --> 00:06:59.340
you have a theoretical prediction.
像是根據一個理論預測，找些人做了實驗

115
00:06:59.340 --> 00:07:02.320
And it's not supported by the data.
不過結果不符合預測

116
00:07:02.320 --> 00:07:06.310
Now you can either distrust your
theory itself or you can say,
此時可以捨棄這套理論

117
00:07:06.310 --> 00:07:11.310
well maybe something else that I assumed
was going on didn't happen as I predicted.
也可以認為實驗過程沒有做好

118
00:07:11.310 --> 00:07:14.690
For example, maybe your
participants were very, very tired.
像是找到的參與者精神狀態都很差

119
00:07:14.690 --> 00:07:17.900
They didn't process all
the information you provided.
無法處理好實驗過程中的訊息

120
00:07:17.900 --> 00:07:21.870
And as a consequence, you didn't
observe the effect that you predicted.
以致於結果不如預期

121
00:07:21.870 --> 00:07:25.210
Now in these situations,
you might not throw away your theory.
若是如此
還不必拋棄理論

122
00:07:25.210 --> 00:07:25.750
You might say,
你可以說

123
00:07:25.750 --> 00:07:29.650
well some of the assumption that I made
about how much attention participants were
是因為實驗操作不符合理論中注意力集中的前提

124
00:07:29.650 --> 00:07:33.250
paying to the experiments,
those assumptions are violated.
需要再試一次

125
00:07:33.250 --> 00:07:37.200
Let's try it again, let's try to boost
the attention levels of participants and
看看注意力集中的參與者表現

126
00:07:37.200 --> 00:07:39.610
see if we can find the expected effect.
會不會符合預測

127
00:07:41.640 --> 00:07:46.300
According to Lakatos, we have a core
theory and around this core theory there's
拉卡托斯主張理論有不可更改的硬核

128
00:07:46.300 --> 00:07:51.410
protective belt of auxiliary hypotheses,
these are assumptions that you make about
以及可調整假設命題的保護帶

129
00:07:51.410 --> 00:07:55.559
the research process and you can give up
some of these assumptions or change them.
研究者可以在過程中修改或放棄保護帶的某些命題

130
00:07:56.570 --> 00:08:00.080
In this sense, you can keep your
core theory, even if your prediction
這樣的主張指出，
若是為了做出更好的預測

131
00:08:00.080 --> 00:08:04.180
doesn't pan out by changing some
of the assumptions that you make.
而調整部分假設，還是能保留硬核

132
00:08:04.180 --> 00:08:05.870
Now, of course, when you do this,
但是如此一來

133
00:08:05.870 --> 00:08:09.830
you enter what's known as
a degenerative research line.
就會進入「退化性研究進程」

134
00:08:09.830 --> 00:08:14.700
It's fine to make an ad hoc assumption
saying, well, it's true but only if.
有時為了提高預測力而提出增加可能條件的後設假設

135
00:08:14.700 --> 00:08:17.380
But if you have to keep doing this and
keep doing this,
但長久為之，理論將不再能提出新的預測

